    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-06-29T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-06-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="30"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d30">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 863.0011/9.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">President</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Emperor</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">The White House</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-06-29">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 29, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Deeply shocked at the atrocious murder of His Imperial and Royal Highness the
                    Archduke Francis Ferdinand and Consort at an assassin’s hands, I extend to Your
                    Majesty, to the Imperial and Royal Family, and to the Government of
                    Austria-Hungary the sincere condolences of the Government and people of the
                    United States and an expression of my own profound sympathy.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Woodrow Wilson</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
